1.
FILTER(Sales, Sales[Amount] > 1000)
→ Returns a table with only the rows from the Sales table where Amount > 1000.

2.

High Sales = CALCULATE(SUM(Sales[Amount]), FILTER(Sales, Sales[Amount] > 1000))


3.

ALL(Sales) removes all filters from the Sales table.

ALLEXCEPT(Sales, Sales[Region]) removes all filters except Region, preserving regional context.

4.

Amount Category = 
SWITCH(TRUE(),
    Sales[Amount] > 1000, "High",
    Sales[Amount] >= 500, "Medium",
    "Low"
)


5.
ALLSELECTED returns all values visible through slicers, but respects user selections, unlike ALL, which ignores everything.

6.

Regional Sales % = 
DIVIDE(
    SUM(Sales[Amount]),
    CALCULATE(SUM(Sales[Amount]), ALLEXCEPT(Sales, Sales[Region]))
)


7.

Dynamic Measure = 
SWITCH(
    SELECTEDVALUE(Metric[Type]),
    "Sum", SUM(Sales[Amount]),
    "Average", AVERAGE(Sales[Amount]),
    "Count", COUNT(Sales[Amount])
)


8.

Exclude Furniture Sales = 
CALCULATE(SUM(Sales[Amount]), FILTER(Sales, Products[Category] <> "Furniture"))


9.
ALLSELECTED might behave unexpectedly in a pivot if slicers or visuals are interacting in unexpected ways—like hidden filters still applying behind the scenes.

10.

Total Sales Ignore Region = 
CALCULATE(SUM(Sales[Amount]), ALL(Sales[Region]))


11.
Optimized version of High Sales:

High Sales = CALCULATE(SUM(Sales[Amount]), Sales[Amount] > 1000)
